Text.SourceString: How lovely to see a new face around here!//You can call me <NPCName>Betty</>, dear.
Text.LocalizedString: How lovely to see a new face around here!//You can call me <NPCName>Betty</>, dear.

Text.SourceString: You’re the first visitor we’ve had in a while.//After the oil spill last year, tourists hardly come anymore.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re the first visitor we’ve had in a while.//After the oil spill last year, tourists hardly come anymore.

Text.SourceString: Remember to reuse what you can and recycle what you can’t, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember to reuse what you can and recycle what you can’t, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: You’re right, we don’t have any community recycling machines yet.//<portrait=normal>But all in good time.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re right, we don’t have any community recycling machines yet.//<portrait=normal>But all in good time.

Text.SourceString: Did you know turtles often eat trash? They think it’s plankton or floating seaweed. But they can’t digest it.//<portrait=sad>Eating trash really harms animals.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you know turtles often eat trash? They think it’s plankton or floating seaweed. But they can’t digest it.//<portrait=sad>Eating trash really harms animals.

Text.SourceString: For old folks like me, Monday is just another day.
Text.LocalizedString: For old folks like me, Monday is just another day.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind refilling the bird feeders around town.//I have a lot of time on my hands.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind refilling the bird feeders around town.//I have a lot of time on my hands.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Pablo</> helps me fix the broken bird feeders.//<portrait=happy>He and his brother are very handy.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Pablo</> helps me fix the broken bird feeders.//<portrait=happy>He and his brother are very handy.

Text.SourceString: This island has a lot of potential.//It warms my heart to see people beginning to appreciate it.
Text.LocalizedString: This island has a lot of potential.//It warms my heart to see people beginning to appreciate it.

Text.SourceString: After all, you moved here, didn’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: After all, you moved here, didn’t you?

Text.SourceString: If you have fruit trees on your farm, don’t chop them down at the end of the season.//Unlike crops that die at the end of the season, they’ll be ready to produce again in the coming year.//<portrait=happy>Your grandmother shared that bit of wisdom with me.
Text.LocalizedString: If you have fruit trees on your farm, don’t chop them down at the end of the season.//Unlike crops that die at the end of the season, they’ll be ready to produce again in the coming year.//<portrait=happy>Your grandmother shared that bit of wisdom with me.

Text.SourceString: I thought I’d pass on the information to you.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought I’d pass on the information to you.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. You seem preoccupied, dear.//Everything okay, I hope?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. You seem preoccupied, dear.//Everything okay, I hope?

Text.SourceString: If you’re looking for things to do during Winter, maybe you could take up fishing.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re looking for things to do during Winter, maybe you could take up fishing.

Text.SourceString: I still find joy in baking, but not quite as much as I used to.//<portrait=concerned>I just don’t have the same energy.
Text.LocalizedString: I still find joy in baking, but not quite as much as I used to.//<portrait=concerned>I just don’t have the same energy.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Eva</> and I have a lot in common. We both love red velvet cake.//<portrait=normal>But who doesn’t?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Eva</> and I have a lot in common. We both love red velvet cake.//<portrait=normal>But who doesn’t?

Text.SourceString: She’s such a ray of sunshine.//I always look forward to having Sunday tea with her.
Text.LocalizedString: She’s such a ray of sunshine.//I always look forward to having Sunday tea with her.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>? Hmm… Are you all right?
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>? Hmm… Are you all right?

Text.SourceString: Don’t strain yourself. I need to drink more water in Summer, even though I do the same tasks every season of the year.//Make sure you do that too.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t strain yourself. I need to drink more water in Summer, even though I do the same tasks every season of the year.//Make sure you do that too.

Text.SourceString: I’m not entirely against plastics. I have plenty of plastic things in my kitchen.//I find ways to reuse them.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not entirely against plastics. I have plenty of plastic things in my kitchen.//I find ways to reuse them.

Text.SourceString: Not just plastic, tin cans too.//<portrait=normal>They make excellent containers for crackers.
Text.LocalizedString: Not just plastic, tin cans too.//<portrait=normal>They make excellent containers for crackers.

Text.SourceString: The kids run the Tavern on their own.//It may look easy, but running a food business is a lot of work.
Text.LocalizedString: The kids run the Tavern on their own.//It may look easy, but running a food business is a lot of work.

Text.SourceString: I try not to meddle too much.//I believe they've got the Tavern under control.
Text.LocalizedString: I try not to meddle too much.//I believe they've got the Tavern under control.

Text.SourceString: When I visit the school, I talk about many things.//<portrait=normal>Like how to recycle properly, for example.//It might seem straightforward, but it's crucial for the kids to learn it right.
Text.LocalizedString: When I visit the school, I talk about many things.//<portrait=normal>Like how to recycle properly, for example.//It might seem straightforward, but it's crucial for the kids to learn it right.

Text.SourceString: Hopefully, they carry these lessons into their adulthood.
Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, they carry these lessons into their adulthood.

Text.SourceString: Are you eating enough, dear?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you eating enough, dear?

Text.SourceString: My only advice is to keep experimenting with your cooking.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Frank</> always has an eye out for new recipes to try.
Text.LocalizedString: My only advice is to keep experimenting with your cooking.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Frank</> always has an eye out for new recipes to try.

Text.SourceString: I miss the old days sometimes, don’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: I miss the old days sometimes, don’t you?

Text.SourceString: Can’t answer that one?//Maybe your old days are different from the ones I remember.
Text.LocalizedString: Can’t answer that one?//Maybe your old days are different from the ones I remember.

Text.SourceString: If you plant bee-friendly flowers on your farm, it can really boost the bee population.//And if you could set up a few bee houses, that'd be the cherry on top.
Text.LocalizedString: If you plant bee-friendly flowers on your farm, it can really boost the bee population.//And if you could set up a few bee houses, that'd be the cherry on top.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Noah</> says I spoil the cats, <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>.//<portrait=happy>I’m starting to think he might have a point.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Noah</> says I spoil the cats, <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>.//<portrait=happy>I’m starting to think he might have a point.

Text.SourceString: You might consider storing a part of your harvest for later.
Text.LocalizedString: You might consider storing a part of your harvest for later.

Text.SourceString: Oh, why, you ask? Well, perhaps for a nice meal in the future? You never know.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, why, you ask? Well, perhaps for a nice meal in the future? You never know.

Text.SourceString: Kids are very perceptive.//They absorb everything we do like little sponges.//As grown-ups, it's up to us to show them the right way.
Text.LocalizedString: Kids are very perceptive.//They absorb everything we do like little sponges.//As grown-ups, it's up to us to show them the right way.

Text.SourceString: It’s the same way with cats. They’re very smart.//We also need to be a good example for them.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the same way with cats. They’re very smart.//We also need to be a good example for them.

Text.SourceString: Yesterday, I taught about all the different things that damage coral reefs and how to prevent the reefs from dying.
Text.LocalizedString: Yesterday, I taught about all the different things that damage coral reefs and how to prevent the reefs from dying.

Text.SourceString: I volunteer at the school each week.//<portrait=normal>It's a little something I share with my daughter-in-law, <NpcName>Erika</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I volunteer at the school each week.//<portrait=normal>It's a little something I share with my daughter-in-law, <NpcName>Erika</>.

Text.SourceString: It’s our responsibility to take care of the planet for future generations.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s our responsibility to take care of the planet for future generations.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… I’m going to try to make a batch of popiah sometime this week.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… I’m going to try to make a batch of popiah sometime this week.

Text.SourceString: I wonder how many carrots we have left in the fridge.//<portrait=sad>I know we have some eggplants, but you can’t use eggplants to make popiah.//<portrait=annoyed>It wouldn’t be popiah without carrots.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder how many carrots we have left in the fridge.//<portrait=sad>I know we have some eggplants, but you can’t use eggplants to make popiah.//<portrait=annoyed>It wouldn’t be popiah without carrots.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Noah</> needs to be more careful when he puts dishes away.//We almost lost a stack of cups the other day when he crammed the cabinet too full.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Noah</> needs to be more careful when he puts dishes away.//We almost lost a stack of cups the other day when he crammed the cabinet too full.

Text.SourceString: I like a lot of things about this town.//<portrait=happy>The lake, the wildlife, <NpcName>Jim’s</> smoked salmon.
Text.LocalizedString: I like a lot of things about this town.//<portrait=happy>The lake, the wildlife, <NpcName>Jim’s</> smoked salmon.

Text.SourceString: Now, remember to give your fresh produce a good rinse under running water before you eat them, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Now, remember to give your fresh produce a good rinse under running water before you eat them, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: We wouldn’t want to be munching on dirt, now would we?
Text.LocalizedString: We wouldn’t want to be munching on dirt, now would we?

Text.SourceString: Be careful of crows. They may seem harmless, but they like to steal crops.
Text.LocalizedString: Be careful of crows. They may seem harmless, but they like to steal crops.

Text.SourceString: If you’re worried, I hear scarecrows can be effective.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re worried, I hear scarecrows can be effective.

Text.SourceString: A community garden reminds me of the old days, when we used to share everything we had.
Text.LocalizedString: A community garden reminds me of the old days, when we used to share everything we had.

Text.SourceString: My great-grandparents were part of the farming community on this island. They planted, while others fished or built.
Text.LocalizedString: My great-grandparents were part of the farming community on this island. They planted, while others fished or built.

Text.SourceString: Peonies are blooming this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: Peonies are blooming this time of year.

Text.SourceString: Will you be planting any at your farm?//<portrait=normal>It’s not too late, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: Will you be planting any at your farm?//<portrait=normal>It’s not too late, you know.

Text.SourceString: I’ll be bringing red velvet cake tomorrow. I suspect there won’t be many desserts.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll be bringing red velvet cake tomorrow. I suspect there won’t be many desserts.

Text.SourceString: I was talking about the Cherry Blossom Festival. What were you talking about, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: I was talking about the Cherry Blossom Festival. What were you talking about, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: You'll find a handy little calendar in front of <NpcName>Sam’s</> store. It's got all the festivals and birthdays.//<portrait=normal>Do give it a look. Quite helpful, I must say.
Text.LocalizedString: You'll find a handy little calendar in front of <NpcName>Sam’s</> store. It's got all the festivals and birthdays.//<portrait=normal>Do give it a look. Quite helpful, I must say.

Text.SourceString: I'm trying to help the bees by planting flowers.//Hopefully, in time, we'll see more bee houses popping up around the island.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm trying to help the bees by planting flowers.//Hopefully, in time, we'll see more bee houses popping up around the island.

Text.SourceString: Am I really going to complain about the heat?//<portrait=annoyed>No. I will not.
Text.LocalizedString: Am I really going to complain about the heat?//<portrait=annoyed>No. I will not.

Text.SourceString: It <Italic>is</> warm…//But warm is good.//<portrait=normal>We need warmth sometimes, yes?//<portrait=annoyed>The humidity, though… Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: It <Italic>is</> warm…//But warm is good.//<portrait=normal>We need warmth sometimes, yes?//<portrait=annoyed>The humidity, though… Hmm…

Text.SourceString: It’s too hot for tulips.//<portrait=annoyed>I think I’ll plant irises instead.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s too hot for tulips.//<portrait=annoyed>I think I’ll plant irises instead.

Text.SourceString: Sunflowers are blooming this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: Sunflowers are blooming this time of year.

Text.SourceString: Are you thinking of growing any on your farm, dear?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you thinking of growing any on your farm, dear?

Text.SourceString: I can’t be outside in the heat for too long. The heat can be…a bit much.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t be outside in the heat for too long. The heat can be…a bit much.

Text.SourceString: I never get tired of the Fall breeze.//Ah… This is my favorite time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: I never get tired of the Fall breeze.//Ah… This is my favorite time of year.

Text.SourceString: Keep some lotuses in your pantry, <PlayerName>$player</>. You never know when you’ll have a craving for mooncakes.
Text.LocalizedString: Keep some lotuses in your pantry, <PlayerName>$player</>. You never know when you’ll have a craving for mooncakes.

Text.SourceString: Raising four children isn’t easy. Especially when they’re so close in age. It was chaos from the first, but I wouldn’t change it for the world.
Text.LocalizedString: Raising four children isn’t easy. Especially when they’re so close in age. It was chaos from the first, but I wouldn’t change it for the world.

Text.SourceString: I sometimes wish <NPCName>Frank</> would give me some grandchildren! But I respect their decision.//<portrait=normal>There’s always <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I sometimes wish <NPCName>Frank</> would give me some grandchildren! But I respect their decision.//<portrait=normal>There’s always <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>.

Text.SourceString: Making mooncakes isn’t that tough. All you need is a lotus, mix it with flour and egg, and give it a good blend.//You should give it a try!
Text.LocalizedString: Making mooncakes isn’t that tough. All you need is a lotus, mix it with flour and egg, and give it a good blend.//You should give it a try!

Text.SourceString: The weather keeps getting colder. It’s not agreeing with my joints.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather keeps getting colder. It’s not agreeing with my joints.

Text.SourceString: Oh dear me.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh dear me.

Text.SourceString: *coughs*
Text.LocalizedString: *coughs*

Text.SourceString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.
Text.LocalizedString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.

Text.SourceString: Your boots are soaking, dear.//Would you please wipe them off at the door?
Text.LocalizedString: Your boots are soaking, dear.//Would you please wipe them off at the door?

Text.SourceString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.
Text.LocalizedString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.

Text.SourceString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.
Text.LocalizedString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.

Text.SourceString: You should go home and rest, dear.//With this weather, you have to be careful not to catch a cold.
Text.LocalizedString: You should go home and rest, dear.//With this weather, you have to be careful not to catch a cold.

Text.SourceString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.
Text.LocalizedString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.

Text.SourceString: Would you wipe your boots at the door, please?
Text.LocalizedString: Would you wipe your boots at the door, please?

Text.SourceString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.
Text.LocalizedString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.

Text.SourceString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.
Text.LocalizedString: If I don’t absolutely have to leave the house, I try to stay in when the weather’s like this.

Text.SourceString: Is it snowing out?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it snowing out?

Text.SourceString: The kids must be out building snowmen by the park.//<portrait=normal>It used to be the favorite spot for all my kids when it snowed. Heh heh.
Text.LocalizedString: The kids must be out building snowmen by the park.//<portrait=normal>It used to be the favorite spot for all my kids when it snowed. Heh heh.

Text.SourceString: The snow is giving me cold feet…
Text.LocalizedString: The snow is giving me cold feet…

Text.SourceString: I have to wear extra socks at night.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to wear extra socks at night.

Text.SourceString: What a lovely day!//<portrait=happy>I might bake mooncakes to enjoy with some evening tea.
Text.LocalizedString: What a lovely day!//<portrait=happy>I might bake mooncakes to enjoy with some evening tea.

Text.SourceString: Why, of course I can bake mooncakes.//I don’t just bake cookies, dear.
Text.LocalizedString: Why, of course I can bake mooncakes.//I don’t just bake cookies, dear.

Text.SourceString: Please watch your step. I’d hate for you to crush these flowers.
Text.LocalizedString: Please watch your step. I’d hate for you to crush these flowers.

Text.SourceString: Are you heading to the beach?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you heading to the beach?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Millie</> is the only one who’s building a house in this area. I wonder why it isn’t more popular.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Millie</> is the only one who’s building a house in this area. I wonder why it isn’t more popular.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been trying to get <NPCName>Frank</> to eat more yogurt.//He’s been eating pancakes all the time lately, and <NpcName>Erika</> doesn’t seem to pay much attention to their diet at home.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been trying to get <NPCName>Frank</> to eat more yogurt.//He’s been eating pancakes all the time lately, and <NpcName>Erika</> doesn’t seem to pay much attention to their diet at home.

Text.SourceString: He and <NpcName>Noah</> are picky when it comes to yogurt.//<portrait=sad>No matter what I put in it, they don’t seem to like it.
Text.LocalizedString: He and <NpcName>Noah</> are picky when it comes to yogurt.//<portrait=sad>No matter what I put in it, they don’t seem to like it.

Text.SourceString: I suppose I can’t blame them.//They’re still young, and they think they’ll be healthy forever.//<portrait=normal>But we need to take care of our bodies so our bodies take care of us, yes?
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose I can’t blame them.//They’re still young, and they think they’ll be healthy forever.//<portrait=normal>But we need to take care of our bodies so our bodies take care of us, yes?

Text.SourceString: I’m enjoying the view.//<portrait=normal>I was foraging in the woodland earlier, and I think I gathered enough for dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m enjoying the view.//<portrait=normal>I was foraging in the woodland earlier, and I think I gathered enough for dinner.

Text.SourceString: If you feel comfortable in the forest, the area around <NpcName>Kira’s</> cabin is very lush.//<portrait=normal>My late husband used to find plenty of things there.
Text.LocalizedString: If you feel comfortable in the forest, the area around <NpcName>Kira’s</> cabin is very lush.//<portrait=normal>My late husband used to find plenty of things there.

Text.SourceString: Have you gone diving lately, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you gone diving lately, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I must be extra careful walking around here.//One fall and I could break my hip.
Text.LocalizedString: I must be extra careful walking around here.//One fall and I could break my hip.

Text.SourceString: Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm…

Text.SourceString: Many fond memories were made here at the beach with my late husband.//Money has never held much value to me.//It's quality time spent with family that truly warms the heart.
Text.LocalizedString: Many fond memories were made here at the beach with my late husband.//Money has never held much value to me.//It's quality time spent with family that truly warms the heart.

Text.SourceString: We used to watch the sunsets together, right there by that old tree.//I always remind my children to cherish the moment, to truly live.//<portrait=happy>One must never be too busy for little adventures.
Text.LocalizedString: We used to watch the sunsets together, right there by that old tree.//I always remind my children to cherish the moment, to truly live.//<portrait=happy>One must never be too busy for little adventures.

Text.SourceString: The wind does seem to have a bit of a bite today.//I should be getting back soon.
Text.LocalizedString: The wind does seem to have a bit of a bite today.//I should be getting back soon.

Text.SourceString: Where’s your wetsuit? It’s perfect diving weather.
Text.LocalizedString: Where’s your wetsuit? It’s perfect diving weather.

Text.SourceString: I’m just here to refill the bird feeder.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just here to refill the bird feeder.

Text.SourceString: Ah, this one still seems to have plenty.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe <NPCName>Suki</> just refilled them.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, this one still seems to have plenty.//<portrait=concerned>Maybe <NPCName>Suki</> just refilled them.

Text.SourceString: Mayor <NpcName>Connor</> put me in charge of the town’s decorations and landscaping.//I like doing it, but it’s a lot of work.//<portrait=happy>Thankfully, I have <NpcName>Pablo</> to help.
Text.LocalizedString: Mayor <NpcName>Connor</> put me in charge of the town’s decorations and landscaping.//I like doing it, but it’s a lot of work.//<portrait=happy>Thankfully, I have <NpcName>Pablo</> to help.

Text.SourceString: Now that I have a lot of free time on my hands, I can finally give back to the community.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that I have a lot of free time on my hands, I can finally give back to the community.

Text.SourceString: Are you stopping by the Tavern?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you stopping by the Tavern?

Text.SourceString: Today I want to focus on the town’s landscaping.
Text.LocalizedString: Today I want to focus on the town’s landscaping.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind helping to sort the recyclables.//<portrait=normal>With my children all grown up, it’s nice to feel needed sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind helping to sort the recyclables.//<portrait=normal>With my children all grown up, it’s nice to feel needed sometimes.

Text.SourceString: My youngest son, <NpcName>Eddy</>, hasn’t answered my last letter after a week. It’s nothing out of the ordinary for him.//It doesn’t keep me from worrying every time he does it, though.
Text.LocalizedString: My youngest son, <NpcName>Eddy</>, hasn’t answered my last letter after a week. It’s nothing out of the ordinary for him.//It doesn’t keep me from worrying every time he does it, though.

Text.SourceString: Good thing <NpcName>Aaliyah</> keeps a close watch on him.//<portrait=concerned>I just wish he’d call more often.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing <NpcName>Aaliyah</> keeps a close watch on him.//<portrait=concerned>I just wish he’d call more often.

Text.SourceString: I’m not worried about what will happen to Fishensips when I–//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Frank</> and <NpcName>Noah</> are doing great running the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not worried about what will happen to Fishensips when I–//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Frank</> and <NpcName>Noah</> are doing great running the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: Besides, they have <NpcName>Aaliyah</> to help if anything were to go south.//<portrait=happy>I know I can count on my girl to watch over her little siblings.
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, they have <NpcName>Aaliyah</> to help if anything were to go south.//<portrait=happy>I know I can count on my girl to watch over her little siblings.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Frank</> is a joker. I see a lot of my late husband in him.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Frank</> is a joker. I see a lot of my late husband in him.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Noah</> – ah, he’s a sensitive soul. He has a gentle heart, that one.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Noah</> – ah, he’s a sensitive soul. He has a gentle heart, that one.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Connor</> has been mayor for as long as I can remember.//He truly cares about Coral Island and the people in it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Connor</> has been mayor for as long as I can remember.//He truly cares about Coral Island and the people in it.

Text.SourceString: Ever since my husband, <NPCName>Frankie</>, passed away, <NPCName>Frank</> has been stepping up a lot.//I pray for that boy. He has a lot on his shoulders.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever since my husband, <NPCName>Frankie</>, passed away, <NPCName>Frank</> has been stepping up a lot.//I pray for that boy. He has a lot on his shoulders.

Text.SourceString: That boy has grown to be a very dependable man. His dad would’ve been proud.
Text.LocalizedString: That boy has grown to be a very dependable man. His dad would’ve been proud.

Text.SourceString: The key to baking is to follow the recipe as closely as possible.//Do that, and you’ll get a perfect result 90 percent of the time.
Text.LocalizedString: The key to baking is to follow the recipe as closely as possible.//Do that, and you’ll get a perfect result 90 percent of the time.

Text.SourceString: Ten percent of success is down to the quality of the ingredients.
Text.LocalizedString: Ten percent of success is down to the quality of the ingredients.

Text.SourceString: My husband and I used to go diving in the middle of the week.// Afterward, we’d always have big bowls of seafood ramen.
Text.LocalizedString: My husband and I used to go diving in the middle of the week.// Afterward, we’d always have big bowls of seafood ramen.

Text.SourceString: It was our seafood day. I looked forward to it every week.
Text.LocalizedString: It was our seafood day. I looked forward to it every week.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Emma</> makes terrific food. She’s great with spices.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Emma</> makes terrific food. She’s great with spices.

Text.SourceString: I’m so proud of her.//<portrait=normal>I still remember when she used to work at <NpcName>Sam’s</>, and now she has a business of her own.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so proud of her.//<portrait=normal>I still remember when she used to work at <NpcName>Sam’s</>, and now she has a business of her own.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if I should wear red to the Cherry Blossom Festival.//It’s a happy day. Thought it might bring some of that same good luck from New Year’s.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if I should wear red to the Cherry Blossom Festival.//It’s a happy day. Thought it might bring some of that same good luck from New Year’s.

Text.SourceString: Happy New Year, dear. I pray this year is good for you, bringing you a lot of fortune and happiness.
Text.LocalizedString: Happy New Year, dear. I pray this year is good for you, bringing you a lot of fortune and happiness.

Text.SourceString: In our house, we never miss eating mooncakes together in Fall.//<portrait=happy>I hope it brings us good luck.
Text.LocalizedString: In our house, we never miss eating mooncakes together in Fall.//<portrait=happy>I hope it brings us good luck.

Text.SourceString: I make sure to always make mooncakes for the Harvest Festival.//It’s good to share them with the people we love.
Text.LocalizedString: I make sure to always make mooncakes for the Harvest Festival.//It’s good to share them with the people we love.

Text.SourceString: My children and I used to sit and watch the moon on Fall nights.//<portrait=normal>I’d tell them tales my mother used to tell me. Like stories about the Moon <NPCName>Goddess</> and her Moon Rabbit.
Text.LocalizedString: My children and I used to sit and watch the moon on Fall nights.//<portrait=normal>I’d tell them tales my mother used to tell me. Like stories about the Moon <NPCName>Goddess</> and her Moon Rabbit.

Text.SourceString: I like to think <NPCName>Frankie</> and I did the best we could raising the kids.//<portrait=normal>We might not have had a lot, but we made sure they always got what they needed.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to think <NPCName>Frankie</> and I did the best we could raising the kids.//<portrait=normal>We might not have had a lot, but we made sure they always got what they needed.

Text.SourceString: A house needs kids’ laughter, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: A house needs kids’ laughter, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: I try to clean the ceramic plates at least once a year. Get them out of the cabinet, wash them, and put them back.//<portrait=happy>Oh, we don’t use them. Only for the New Year’s dinner, at most.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to clean the ceramic plates at least once a year. Get them out of the cabinet, wash them, and put them back.//<portrait=happy>Oh, we don’t use them. Only for the New Year’s dinner, at most.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Aaliyah</> was always a smart kid. Ever since she was a little girl, she got trophies left and right.//Look around, they’re everywhere in this house!
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Aaliyah</> was always a smart kid. Ever since she was a little girl, she got trophies left and right.//Look around, they’re everywhere in this house!

Text.SourceString: There weren’t a lot of books around when I was a little girl.//<portrait=normal>Now kids have books on their computers and phones.
Text.LocalizedString: There weren’t a lot of books around when I was a little girl.//<portrait=normal>Now kids have books on their computers and phones.

Text.SourceString: I used to take the children to visit my parents on New Year’s. Not always, but if we could, we would. This was before, when they were still alive.//It was a good way for the children to spend time with their cousins.//<portrait=concerned>New Year’s visits were important to my parents.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to take the children to visit my parents on New Year’s. Not always, but if we could, we would. This was before, when they were still alive.//It was a good way for the children to spend time with their cousins.//<portrait=concerned>New Year’s visits were important to my parents.

Text.SourceString: You’re a good addition to this community, dear.//<portrait=normal>I’m glad you moved here.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re a good addition to this community, dear.//<portrait=normal>I’m glad you moved here.

Text.SourceString: I used to make my own noodles for birthdays, but now it’s just too much work, especially with four children.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think my hands could take it.//<portrait=normal>Now we just buy noodles to use in my recipes.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to make my own noodles for birthdays, but now it’s just too much work, especially with four children.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think my hands could take it.//<portrait=normal>Now we just buy noodles to use in my recipes.

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to make the rounds. I want to make sure the bird feeders are all full before the end of the week.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m trying to make the rounds. I want to make sure the bird feeders are all full before the end of the week.

Text.SourceString: People around town have been talking about how <NPCName>Frank</>’s cats, <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>, go roaming around at night.//I had no idea they were so adventurous.
Text.LocalizedString: People around town have been talking about how <NPCName>Frank</>’s cats, <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>, go roaming around at night.//I had no idea they were so adventurous.

Text.SourceString: Oh, you heard that too? Ah, I’m worried about them.//Cats out at night – I don’t think it’s very safe. I wish <NPCName>Frank</> would do something about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you heard that too? Ah, I’m worried about them.//Cats out at night – I don’t think it’s very safe. I wish <NPCName>Frank</> would do something about it.

Text.SourceString: The stairs are a little slippery today. I’ll ask <NpcName>Joko</> to take a look. Maybe it’s mold.//Hopefully not. Hopefully, it’s just water or something.
Text.LocalizedString: The stairs are a little slippery today. I’ll ask <NpcName>Joko</> to take a look. Maybe it’s mold.//Hopefully not. Hopefully, it’s just water or something.

Text.SourceString: Thinking about how much Fishensips has seen makes me sad sometimes.//We raised four children in it…the cats…<NPCName>Frankie</>…
Text.LocalizedString: Thinking about how much Fishensips has seen makes me sad sometimes.//We raised four children in it…the cats…<NPCName>Frankie</>…

Text.SourceString: It’s good to have a coffee shop in front of Fishensips. It makes the area lively.//<portrait=happy><NpcName>Raj</> is a good kid too. They know so much about coffee beans.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s good to have a coffee shop in front of Fishensips. It makes the area lively.//<portrait=happy><NpcName>Raj</> is a good kid too. They know so much about coffee beans.

Text.SourceString: We need to stock up on oranges. I’ll be taking some to <NPCName>Frankie</>’s and my parents’ graves soon.//Maybe <NpcName>Noah</> can pick some up from <NpcName>Sam’s</>.
Text.LocalizedString: We need to stock up on oranges. I’ll be taking some to <NPCName>Frankie</>’s and my parents’ graves soon.//Maybe <NpcName>Noah</> can pick some up from <NpcName>Sam’s</>.

Text.SourceString: I watched the twins, <NpcName>Alice</> and <NpcName>Suki</>, grow up.//That girl <NpcName>Alice</> was over at the house every other day, playing with my sons, watching TV.
Text.LocalizedString: I watched the twins, <NpcName>Alice</> and <NpcName>Suki</>, grow up.//That girl <NpcName>Alice</> was over at the house every other day, playing with my sons, watching TV.

Text.SourceString: We used to take her with us to family gatherings. She’s practically family to us.
Text.LocalizedString: We used to take her with us to family gatherings. She’s practically family to us.

Text.SourceString: I was worried when <NPCName>Frank</> was dating that Pokyo girl.//I was afraid he might not want to come back home after university.//<portrait=concerned>With <NpcName>Eddy</> living abroad and <NpcName>Aaliyah</> busy with her duties, I’d be left with just one son to run this place.
Text.LocalizedString: I was worried when <NPCName>Frank</> was dating that Pokyo girl.//I was afraid he might not want to come back home after university.//<portrait=concerned>With <NpcName>Eddy</> living abroad and <NpcName>Aaliyah</> busy with her duties, I’d be left with just one son to run this place.

Text.SourceString: If <NPCName>Frank</> had wanted to stay in Pokyo, I guess it would have been fine.//<portrait=sad>Fishensips is big. It’s too much work for one person, but <NpcName>Noah</> always could have hired help.
Text.LocalizedString: If <NPCName>Frank</> had wanted to stay in Pokyo, I guess it would have been fine.//<portrait=sad>Fishensips is big. It’s too much work for one person, but <NpcName>Noah</> always could have hired help.

Text.SourceString: The water is refreshingly cool today.
Text.LocalizedString: The water is refreshingly cool today.

Text.SourceString: The ocean introduced me to a lot of creatures.//<portrait=happy>Keep diving, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m sure it’ll open up to you, too.
Text.LocalizedString: The ocean introduced me to a lot of creatures.//<portrait=happy>Keep diving, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m sure it’ll open up to you, too.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes when we knock on a door, the one who answers it isn’t who we expected.//<portrait=happy>And that’s okay.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes when we knock on a door, the one who answers it isn’t who we expected.//<portrait=happy>And that’s okay.

Text.SourceString: Just try to be more patient, dear.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes we do forget to show ourselves some kindness.
Text.LocalizedString: Just try to be more patient, dear.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes we do forget to show ourselves some kindness.

Text.SourceString: I should make more bird food.//I'm running a bit low.
Text.LocalizedString: I should make more bird food.//I'm running a bit low.

Text.SourceString: Our community here is close, as tight as a hand-knit sweater. We all know and care for each other.//It's such a lovely feeling to be surrounded by all these friendly faces.
Text.LocalizedString: Our community here is close, as tight as a hand-knit sweater. We all know and care for each other.//It's such a lovely feeling to be surrounded by all these friendly faces.

Text.SourceString: Life has a slower rhythm here, but that's how we enjoy it. We take our time and appreciate every single moment.//<portrait=happy>No need to hurry, dear. There's no rush.
Text.LocalizedString: Life has a slower rhythm here, but that's how we enjoy it. We take our time and appreciate every single moment.//<portrait=happy>No need to hurry, dear. There's no rush.

Text.SourceString: The nearest town is a few hours away by boat, so I only go there when necessary.
Text.LocalizedString: The nearest town is a few hours away by boat, so I only go there when necessary.

Text.SourceString: Living on this small island, it can be tough at times. We have to make do with what we've got, and there's always the worry about the electricity going out during a storm.
Text.LocalizedString: Living on this small island, it can be tough at times. We have to make do with what we've got, and there's always the worry about the electricity going out during a storm.

Text.SourceString: My daughter, she's the light of my life. When she was away in the military, I missed her each and every day.//<portrait=concerned>I was always so worried about her safety and well-being.
Text.LocalizedString: My daughter, she's the light of my life. When she was away in the military, I missed her each and every day.//<portrait=concerned>I was always so worried about her safety and well-being.

Text.SourceString: I try to stay strong and keep a positive spirit, but it's not always easy.//Sometimes, I just get overwhelmed and the tears come.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to stay strong and keep a positive spirit, but it's not always easy.//Sometimes, I just get overwhelmed and the tears come.

Text.SourceString: I’m grateful for <NpcName>Aaliyah’s</> service, and I couldn't be prouder of the woman she's grown into.//I prayed for her safety every day she was away from me.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m grateful for <NpcName>Aaliyah’s</> service, and I couldn't be prouder of the woman she's grown into.//I prayed for her safety every day she was away from me.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard without <NPCName>Frankie</> around.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard without <NPCName>Frankie</> around.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Erika</> always dotes on <NPCName>Butter</>, calling her “Baby <NPCName>Butter</>.” She never uses such a nickname for <NPCName>Peanut</>.//<portrait=annoyed>Don't think I haven't noticed that, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//It seems quite clear to me that she has a favorite.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Erika</> always dotes on <NPCName>Butter</>, calling her “Baby <NPCName>Butter</>.” She never uses such a nickname for <NPCName>Peanut</>.//<portrait=annoyed>Don't think I haven't noticed that, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//It seems quite clear to me that she has a favorite.

Text.SourceString: I don’t always agree with everything <NpcName>Erika</> does, but she’s a sweet girl.//<portrait=happy>She spends a lot of her time teaching kids, doing volunteer work. My son is lucky to have her.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t always agree with everything <NpcName>Erika</> does, but she’s a sweet girl.//<portrait=happy>She spends a lot of her time teaching kids, doing volunteer work. My son is lucky to have her.

Text.SourceString: You might think cats don’t understand you, but I believe they do.//They have feelings too, my dear. I do my best not to favor one over the other.//I wouldn’t want to hurt their feelings.
Text.LocalizedString: You might think cats don’t understand you, but I believe they do.//They have feelings too, my dear. I do my best not to favor one over the other.//I wouldn’t want to hurt their feelings.
